{
  "stem": "23278.2",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I was, you know-- it went to America.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And the Americans turned them out.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And they couldn't land.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And they had to be back to Germany, and of course-- and I remember, people were very-- an officer of the French army with his wife, and group of rich people said that Roosevelt had done well and should have sunk the ship all together so we get rid the all those scoundrels.",
      "word_count": 53
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And you know, I couldn't believe it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "I didn't say anything.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Because as a child, you were not supposed to talk back to grown-ups.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "But I was sick.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was with my mother who was knitting with some other people.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But I happened to be there.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I talked to my father.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And my father said it was the most horrible thing that those people said and the most horrible thing the United States had done.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then we started to-- to worry about that.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Plus those orchestras with those sad eyes and those people who didn't play perfectly-- we knew when they made mistakes.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they felt bad about it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And, you know, the women were in their evening gowns, as supposed to be.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I was envying them to travel from city to city and be all beautiful.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But I wonder why they look so sad.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And then my father explained.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Then it came the '38 to come back to school.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Then came the Crystal Night.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And the Crystal Night, my friend Rita Thalmann wrote the first book about it.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I think it's a classic.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And she mentioned it was November 9th that the German chose for a date for the fall of the Berlin Wall, the 9th of November, when it was not the 9th at all.",
      "word_count": 33
    }
  ],
